Input.document:
The family of Barack Obama, the 44th President of the United States, and his wife Michelle Obama is made up of people of Kenyan (Luo), African-American, and Old Stock American (including originally English, Scottish, Welsh, Irish, French, German, and Swiss) ancestry.

Born circa 1829 in Moneygall, Ireland, he emigrated to Ohio via New York in 1850, making him the most recent immigrant on the maternal side of Barack Obama's family tree.
Answer.answer:
Obama was the 44th President of the US. He's married to Michelle and he has a lot of Kenyan people in his family but also some European ancestry as well.

The most recent person in Obama's family to immigrate to the US was in 1850. It was a man that came from Ireland to Ohio.

When you're buying a home using a mortgage, refinancing your existing mortgage, or selling your home to anyone other than an all-cash buyer, the home appraisal is a key component of the transaction.

Appraisals are almost always used in purchase and sale transactions and commonly used in refinance transactions. In a purchase and sale transaction, an appraisal is used to determine whether the home's contract price is appropriate given the home's condition, location, and features. In a refinance, it assures the lender that it isn't handing the borrower more money than the home is worth.
Answer.answer:
When you purchase a house using a mortgage, are refinancing an existing mortgage, or selling your house, the home appraisal is a key component of your transaction.

Appraisals can be used in purchase and sale transactions and also refinances.  An appraisal is used in a purchase and sale transaction to determine if the home's contract price is appropriate provided the home's condition, location, and features.  For a refinance it give assurance to the lender that they aren't giving the borrower more than the house is worth.

DJs use equipment that can play at least two sources of recorded music simultaneously and mix them together. This allows the DJ to create seamless transitions between recordings and develop unique mixes of songs.

Disc jockeys are people who mix different existing music together as the music is playing; DJs often work in dance clubs, radio, and/or nightclubs.

Input.document:
The Alexians, Alexian Brothers or Cellites are a Catholic religious institute or congregation specifically devoted to caring for the sick which has its origin in Europe at the time of the Black Death.

In the early 20th century the Alexian Brothers had four hospitals in the United States. The first was built in Chicago in 1866; it was destroyed by the Great Fire, on 9 October 1871, and rebuilt the following year.
Answer.answer:
A Catholic religious institute known as the Alexian Brothers or Alexians are singularly devoted to tending to the ill. They came about during the era of the Bubonic plague in Europe, which led to the death of over a third of the continent's population. 

In the previous century, the Alexians built four hospitals in the US. One built in Chicago in 1866 was razed to the ground in 1871 in the Great Fire, and then rebuilt in 1872.

Mount Wilson is one of the better-known peaks of the San Gabriel Mountains, located within the San Gabriel Mountains National Monument and Angeles National Forest in Los Angeles County, California.

The first television antenna on Mount Wilson was erected in 1947 for pioneer station KTLA channel 5. At about the same time, the first FM station broadcast from Mount Wilson, which was the old KFI-FM on 105.9 FM (signed off in 1950).
Answer.answer:
One of the best known peaks in Angeles National Forest is Mount Wilson, part of the San Gabriel Mountains range in Los Angeles County, California. 

Mount Wilson has hosted both television and FM station antennae since 1947. The first TV antenna was for KTLA channel 5 and the first radio antenna was for KFI-FM, 105.9 FM.

Input.document: Estrus, or heat, is the stage in a female dog's reproductive cycle during which she becomes receptive to mating with males. At this time, estrogen levels first increase and then sharply decrease, and mature eggs are released from the ovaries. Ideally, your dog should be spayed before she enters her first heat cycle.
Answer.answer: Female dogs become available for reproduction during a period called estrus, also commonly referred to as heat. A fluctuation in estrogen occurs, increasing and rapidly decreasing, producing mature eggs from the female's ovaries. If you wish to avoid the possibility of your dog becoming pregnant she should be spayed before she enters her first estrus cycle.

Input.document: Estrus, or heat, is the stage in a female dog's reproductive cycle during which she becomes receptive to mating with males. At this time, estrogen levels first increase and then sharply decrease, and mature eggs are released from the ovaries. Ideally, your dog should be spayed before she enters her first heat cycle.
Answer.answer: One of the most important stages in a female dog's reproductive cycle is known as estrus. Also known as "heat," this is the stage at which a female dog's levels of estrogen initially increase and then diminish significantly. At this time, the ovaries release mature eggs, and the female dog becomes the most receptive to mating with other male dogs. It is ideal that a dog be spayed prior to undergoing the first heat cycle.

Input.document: If you own an unspayed female, knowing the symptoms of a dog in heat can be very important to managing her reproductive cycle. Answer.answer: An expensive trip to the vet just to be told your dog is having her cycle can be avoided if you know how to recognize the warning signs. Most females in heat have changes that occur before the spotting everywhere and such changes can range from mood shifts to differences in the amount of food they consume. If you want to remain in control of when your female reproduces, you need to know such symptoms and when they occur.
